snippet: Purchases of existing homes jumped to the highest level in more than three years, an industry group said, exceeding economists’ expectations.
abstract: National Association of Realtors says sales of existing homes jumped in July to the highest level in more than three years, despite rising mortgage interest rates; sales rose 6.5 percent to seasonally adjusted annual rate of 5.39 million units.
lead_paragraph: Purchases of existing homes jumped to the highest level in more than three years, an industry group said, exceeding economists’ expectations.

headline.main: Rising Rates Did Little to Curb July Home Sales
headline.print_headline: Rising Rates Did Little To Curb July Home Sales
